                </h2>
                <p>In literal way, <em>abacus</em> means a counting frame. <em>Abacus</em> was invented for calculation purpose even before the<em> Hindu-Arabic numeral system </em>came to existence, though the exact origin is still unknown.Originally, the abaci were made of stones, they are now being made using bamboo and beads.</p>
               <p class="mb-0">The various designs of the abaci support a variety of mathematical operations ranging from a simple arithmatic computation to a much complicated computations like square roots.In today's world, even though heavy cmputations are taken care of by computers, abaci still remains being used in some countries. Abacus's popularity has grown exceptionally in the last decade. Given the fact that, abacus rquires the children to play around the numbers, parents prefer the abacus way to teach numbers to their kids starting from an early age.</p>
